			<sawd:htmlView name="HTML 6" duid="0oaouic28aft8dk3">
				<sawd:HTML fmt="html" captionID="kcap12832459_2458">&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Description :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; A report can show information sourced from Flat Files model, and, as users drills down a logical hierarchy, transparently switch to relational source. When a level of detail is reached in the hierarchy drill, that is not supported by aggregated source, OBIEE server automatically switches to relational model to source the corresponding detailed data.&lt;br/&gt;
The report shows detail of revenue for product and  time hierarchy. The underlying Flat Files grain is at the month level for time, and product level for product.&lt;br/&gt;
- If the time hierachy column is not expanded below the month level, OBIEE server will only generate queries to Flat Files for fulfilling this report.[br/]
- As soon as detail below month level (week, day) is expanded in the time hierarchy, then the server will retrieve data from the relational source to provide the details.[br/]
You can check the phyisical SQL logs generated in both cases to see the difference.</sawd:HTML>
			</sawd:htmlView>
			
